    "## Imports of the necessary packages"
   ]
  },

    "import gc\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "import urllib.request\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib.colors import LinearSegmentedColormap\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import torchvision.transforms.functional as F\n",
    "from torchvision.transforms import Resize, CenterCrop\n",
    "from torchvision.models import resnet50, ResNet50_Weights\n",
    "from captum.attr import IntegratedGradients, Occlusion, NoiseTunnel, visualization as viz\n",
    "from EnsembleXAI import Ensemble, Metrics"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {

   "source": [
    "## Setting paths to downloaded dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "Below are some paths linking to data. Adjust them according to your directory setup. Data download process is available in `Imagenet_data_prep.ipynb` in the notebooks folder in repo ([link](https://github.com/MattS0000/XAI_ensemblings_BS_MS/blob/main/notebooks/Imagenet_data_prep.ipynb))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 42,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "input_dir = \"\\\\\".join(os.getcwd().split(sep=\"\\\\\")[:-2] + ['input'])\n",
    "#Correct path to masks and input is crucial, setup depends on users download path of the masks\n",
    "masks_dir = input_dir + f'\\\\ImageNetS50\\\\train-semi-segmentation\\\\'\n",
    "images_dir = \"\\\\\".join(os.getcwd().split(sep=\"\\\\\")[:-1] + ['notebooks', 'images']) + \"\\\\\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "source": [
    "We can find natural names for each class id under this link."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 43,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "with urllib.request.urlopen(\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/deep-learning-models/image-models/imagenet_class_index.json\") as url:\n",
    "    imagenet_classes_dict = json.load(url)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "source": [
    "Helper functions to hasten the loading and the required image transformations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 44,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def download_class_images(class_id, masks_path):\n",
    "    full_path = os.path.join(masks_path, class_id)\n",
    "    kaggle_path = f\"/ILSVRC/Data/CLS-LOC/train/{class_id}/\"\n",
    "    for file_name in os.listdir(full_path):\n",
    "        file_name_jpeg = file_name[:-3] + 'JPEG'\n",
    "        !kaggle competitions download -f {kaggle_path}{file_name_jpeg} -p ./images/{class_id}/ -c imagenet-object-localization-challenge\n",
    "\n",
    "def images_list(image_path, resize=True):\n",
    "    _crop = CenterCrop(224).forward\n",
    "    _resize = Resize([232,232]).forward\n",
    "    images = []\n",
    "    for image_name in os.listdir(image_path):\n",
    "        image = Image.open(os.path.join(image_path, image_name))\n",
    "        if resize:\n",
    "            image = _crop(_resize(image))\n",
    "        images.append(image)\n",
    "    return images\n",
    "\n",
    "def load_all(classid):\n",
    "    all_img = images_list(os.path.join(images_dir, classid))[:3]\n",
    "    all_img_org = images_list(os.path.join(images_dir, classid), resize=False)[:3]\n",
    "    all_tens = [F.to_tensor(img) for img in all_img]\n",
    "    all_msks = [(F.to_tensor(img)>0).float() for img in images_list(os.path.join(masks_dir, classid))[:3]]\n",
    "    tens_img = torch.stack(all_tens)\n",
    "    tens_msks = torch.stack(all_msks)\n",
    "    return all_img, all_img_org, all_tens, all_msks, tens_img, tens_msks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "source": [
    "## Loading images and plotting the examples\n",
    "First setting up correct paths to masks and images is required. Masks are the ImageNetS50 masks found on (https://lusseg.github.io/, available under https://github.com/LUSSeg/ImageNet-S/releases/download/ImageNet-S/ImageNetS50-a0fe9d82231f9bc4787ee76e304dfa51.zip), consisting of 10 pixel-perfect masks for each of 50 classes sampled from the imagenet dataset. For sake of easier visualization, we consider 3 images from the \"n01491361\" class which is a tiger shark class."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#download single image from kaggle api, also available in func download_class_images()\n",
    "os.mkdir(os.path.join('images'))\n",
    "os.mkdir(os.path.join('images/n01491361'))\n",
    "!kaggle competitions download -f \"/ILSVRC/Data/CLS-LOC/train/n01491361/n01491361_1000.JPEG\" -p ./images/n01491361/ -c imagenet-object-localization-challenge"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "id = \"n01491361\"\n",
    "all_images, all_images_original, all_tensors, all_masks, tensor_images, tensor_masks = load_all(\"n01491361\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 48,
   "metadata": {

     "output_type": "display_data"

   "source": [
    "photos = []\n",
    "for tensor, mask in zip(all_tensors, all_masks):\n",
    "    photo = torch.cat([tensor, mask], dim=2)\n",
    "    photos.append(photo)\n",
    "display(F.to_pil_image(torch.cat(photos, dim=1)))"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {

   },
   "source": [
    "## Model Loading\n",
    "We use the resnet50 model pretrained on the imagenet dataset and generate predictions on our three images."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 49,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model = resnet50(weights=ResNet50_Weights.DEFAULT)\n",
    "model.eval()\n",
    "resnet_transform = ResNet50_Weights.DEFAULT.transforms()\n",
    "pipeline = lambda images: torch.stack([resnet_transform(image) for image in images])\n",
    "proper_data = pipeline(all_images_original)\n",
    "outputs = model(proper_data)\n",
    "_, preds = torch.max(outputs, 1)\n",
    "probs2 = torch.nn.functional.softmax(outputs, dim=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "source": [
    "## Single Explanations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 50,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x600 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "single_pred = preds[2].unsqueeze(dim=0)\n",
    "single_data = proper_data[2].unsqueeze(dim=0)\n",
    "integrated_gradients = IntegratedGradients(model)\n",
    "attributions_ig = integrated_gradients.attribute(single_data, target=single_pred, n_steps=200)\n",
    "gc.collect()\n",
    "transformed_img = resnet_transform(all_images_original[2])\n",
    "default_cmap = LinearSegmentedColormap.from_list('custom blue',\n",
    "                                                 [(0, '#ffffff'),\n",
    "                                                  (0.25, '#000000'),\n",
    "                                                  (1, '#000000')], N=256)\n",
    "_1 = viz.visualize_image_attr_multiple(np.transpose(attributions_ig.squeeze().numpy(), (1,2,0)),\n",
    "                                      np.transpose(tensor_images[2].squeeze().numpy(), (1,2,0)),\n",
    "                                      [\"heat_map\", \"original_image\"],\n",
    "                                      [\"positive\", \"all\"],\n",
    "                                      cmap=default_cmap,\n",
    "                                      show_colorbar=True,\n",
    "                                      outlier_perc=1)"
   ]

    "                                           target = preds,\n",

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def sample_xai(images):\n",
    "    if images.shape[0] == 1:\n",
    "        target = single_pred\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        target = single_pred.repeat(images.shape[0])\n",
    "    xai = occlusion.attribute(images,\n",
    "                              strides = (3, 40, 40),\n",
    "                              target=target,\n",
    "                              sliding_window_shapes=(3,50, 50),\n",
    "                              baselines=0)\n",
    "    return xai\n",
    "Metrics.stability(sample_xai, single_data.squeeze(dim=0), single_data.repeat(10,1,1,1))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "source": [
    "## Ensembles\n",
    "Ensembling with the normEnsembleXAI functions across the 3 explanations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 64,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "all_stacked = torch.stack([attributions_ig_nt_all, attributions_occ_all_15, attributions_occ_all_25], dim=1)\n",
    "aggreg_all1 = Ensemble.normEnsembleXAI(all_stacked, aggregating_func='avg')\n",
    "aggreg_all2 = Ensemble.normEnsembleXAI(all_stacked, aggregating_func='min')\n",
    "aggreg_all3 = Ensemble.normEnsembleXAI(all_stacked, aggregating_func='max')\n",
    "explanations_all = torch.cat([all_stacked,aggreg_all3.unsqueeze(dim=1), aggreg_all2.unsqueeze(dim=1), aggreg_all1.unsqueeze(dim=1)], dim=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "source": [
    "Consistency metric without and with the ensemblings."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 65,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },

   "source": [
    "## Plotting all explanations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 73,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.style.use('fast')\n",
    "# helper function for the plotting\n",
    "def plot_explanations(images, explanations, columns_names, classes_predicted, method = \"heat_map\"):\n",
    "    cmaps=[default_cmap, None, None, None, None, None, None]\n",
    "    nrow, ncol = len(images), explanations.shape[1]+1\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows = nrow, ncols = ncol, figsize=(14, 3*explanations.shape[0]))\n",
    "    for col, col_name in zip(ax[0], columns_names):\n",
    "        col.title.set_text(col_name)\n",
    "    for i, img in enumerate(images):\n",
    "        ax[i,0].xaxis.set_ticks_position(\"none\")\n",
    "        ax[i,0].yaxis.set_ticks_position(\"none\")\n",
    "        ax[i,0].set_yticklabels([])\n",
    "        ax[i,0].set_xticklabels([])\n",
    "        ax[i,0].imshow(np.array(img), vmin=0, vmax=255)\n",
    "        ax[i,0].set_ylabel(classes_predicted[i], size='large')\n",
    "        for j, col in enumerate(ax[i,1:]):\n",
    "            expl = explanations[i,j]\n",
    "            sign = \"positive\"\n",
    "            if expl.amin() < 0:\n",
    "                sign = \"all\"\n",
    "            _ = viz.visualize_image_attr(np.transpose(expl.squeeze().numpy(), (1,2,0)),\n",
    "                                         original_image=np.array(img),\n",
    "                                         method=method,\n",
    "                                         sign=sign,\n",
    "                                         plt_fig_axis=(fig, col),\n",
    "                                         show_colorbar=True,\n",
    "                                         outlier_perc=2,\n",
    "                                         cmap=cmaps[j],\n",
    "                                         use_pyplot=False\n",
    "                                         )\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 83,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
